com.emmes.aps.util

Class DataTransferUtils

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.emmes.aps.util.DataTransferUtils

  • public final class DataTransferUtils
extends java.lang.Object
    Defines app-wide constants and utilities. Data status is maintained for local data sync with server. When the data is inserted or the insertion part is going on, The status is defined as Incomplete or I. When the data is ready for sync because the date is expired or the user submit button is pressed, The data status becomes Ready to Sync (S). When the data is trying to send some data to server over the network, The data transfer may fail or may succeed, but need to keep track of that. The data which was in transition state is represents with the status IN_QUEUE (Q). If data transfer successfully, The status is set as Complete or C
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Mahbubur Rahman
